From 3c8d055dec4d4d9c9ef34e7ec222e8ed02e7da9a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaradhana Sahu <aaradhana.sahu@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 21 Jul 2025 12:39:42 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] UPSTREAM:CP: wifi: ath12k: Enable pdev suspend and resume
 command

The pdev suspend command helps reduce power consumption. When the last
vdev on a particular pdev is deleted, the host sends a
WMI_PDEV_SUSPEND_CMDID to the firmware. In response, the firmware sends
back a WMI_PDEV_SUSPEND_EVENTID to the host.

Similarly, when the first vdev is created and the corresponding pdev is
in suspend mode, the host sends a WMI_PDEV_RESUME_CMDID to the firmware.
The firmware then responds with a WMI_PDEV_RESUME_EVENTID.

Patch-dependency: "UPSTREAM:CP:wifi:ath12k: ErP support"
Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Aaradhana Sahu <aaradhana.sahu@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
